of the New York Yearly Meeting, Religious Society of Friends. it won the
brainchild almost seven years before
of the Westbury (Lang island) Friends
Meeting. The guidelines set up by the
New York Yearly Meeting calculated
that FWI be: 1) A four year liberal
arts college Quaker in spirit; 2) A
world college, international in character and outreach. in 1965 the State of
New York granted to rwr a promotional
charter which lists for five years, our»
ing which time the school is being developed into Friends World College.
Degrees granted during the time that
FM is not officially a college will
he alternatively dedicated when FWI
