tables pending the outcome of a std.
sent references.
The improvement proceedings were
brought against Smith by Roger Christen»
sen, Vice chairman of the Senate. The
proceedings started'froirl a story released by the Iowa State Daily, which
stated that Smith had attended a party
where marijuana was looked and
that a photographer from Life magaZine was also present. it would ap—
year that the resolution of improvement
is only the most recent episode in a
power struggle which has engaged several members of the ISU Government
of the Student Body (GSB) ever since
Smith’s election.
Tuesday, March 16, Smith appeared,
glad in sweatshirt, learned, cordless.
and related, to deliver his State of
the Campus Address to the student
senate. He customized current trends in
university education. “automatically,"
